Leicester City boss, Brendan Rodgers, has rated AS Roma coach, Jose Mourinho as one of the greatest managers in our present generation. Rodgers said this during his pre-match press conference ahead of Leicester City’s UEFA Europa Conference League semi-final tie with Roma on Thursday. Leicester will host Mourinho’s men on Thursday night in the Europa Conference League last-4 first-leg tie at the King Power Stadium. “He’s one of the great managers. He has nothing ever to prove to anyone,” Rodgers said of Mourinho. “He’s a winner. He will always be a winner. “He will always just have to want to prove it to himself. And I can’t speak any more highly of him.”